| data8    = 1
}}
[[File:Naturalis_Biodiversity_Center_-_RMNH.MAM.33160.b_ven_-_Rhinolophus_sinicus_-_skin.jpeg|thumb]]為自中華菊頭蝠身上發現]]
菊頭蝠為多種[[冠狀病毒|冠狀病毒]]的[[自然宿主|自然宿主]]。2003年[[SARS事件|SARS事件]]後，研究人員在中國各地的多種菊頭蝠身上發現與[[SARS-CoV|SARS-CoV]]相似的病毒株（[[SARSr-CoV|SARSr-CoV]]），以自[[中華菊頭蝠|中華菊頭蝠]]樣本中發現的最多，也有自馬鐵菊頭蝠、[[大耳菊頭蝠|大耳菊頭蝠]]、小菊頭蝠、[[中菊頭蝠|中菊頭蝠]]與{{le|布腊氏菊头蝠|Rhinolophus blasii}}樣本中發現者<ref name="Luk">{{cite journal |doi=10.1016/j.meegid.2019.03.001 |pmid=30844511 |title=Molecular epidemiology, evolution and phylogeny of SARS coronavirus |journal=Infection, Genetics and Evolution |volume=71 |pages=21–30 |year=2019 |last1=Luk|first1=Hayes K.H. |last2=Li |first2=Xin |last3=Fung |first3=Joshua |last4=Lau |first4=Susanna K.P. |last5=Woo|first5=Patrick C.Y.|pmc=7106202 |doi-access=free }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1016/j.virusres.2007.03.012 |pmid=17451830 |title=A review of studies on animal reservoirs of the SARS coronavirus |journal=Virus Research|volume=133 |issue=1|pages=74–87 |year=2008 |last1=Shi |first1=Zhengli |last2=Hu |first2=Zhihong|pmc=7114516 |doi-access=free }}</ref>。2005年，研究人員發表了[[蝙蝠冠狀病毒HKU3|HKU3]]、[[Rf1病毒|Rf1]]、[[Rm1病毒|Rm1]]與[[Rp3病毒|Rp3]]等SARS相關病毒株，分別在中華菊頭蝠、馬鐵菊頭蝠、大耳菊頭蝠與[[皮氏菊頭蝠|皮氏菊頭蝠]]身上發現<ref name="Li2005">{{cite journal|last1=Li|first1=W.|title=Bats Are Natural Reservoirs of SARS-Like Coronaviruses|journal=Science|volume=310|issue=5748|year=2005|pages=676–679|issn=0036-8075|doi=10.1126/science.1118391}}</ref><ref name="LauWoo2005">{{cite journal|last1=Lau|first1=S. K. P.|last2=Woo|first2=P. C. Y.|last3=Li|first3=K. S. M.|last4=Huang|first4=Y.|last5=Tsoi|first5=H.-W.|last6=Wong|first6=B. H. L.|last7=Wong|first7=S. S. Y.|last8=Leung|first8=S.-Y.|last9=Chan|first9=K.-H.|last10=Yuen|first10=K.-Y.|title=Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus-like virus in Chinese horseshoe bats|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences|volume=102|issue=39|year=2005|pages=14040–14045|issn=0027-8424|doi=10.1073/pnas.0506735102}}</ref>；2015年又發表了[[WIV1病毒|WIV1]]與[[SHC014病毒|SHC014]]兩病毒株，皆採自中華菊頭蝠，與SARS-CoV的相似度比前述四種病毒株更高<ref name="2013Nature"/>，且可能具[[跨物種感染|跨越物種]]感染人類的潛力<ref name="MenacheryYount2016">{{cite journal|last1=Menachery|first1=Vineet D.|last2=Yount|first2=Boyd L.|last3=Sims|first3=Amy C.|last4=Debbink|first4=Kari|last5=Agnihothram|first5=Sudhakar S.|last6=Gralinski|first6=Lisa E.|last7=Graham|first7=Rachel L.|last8=Scobey|first8=Trevor|last9=Plante|first9=Jessica A.|last10=Royal|first10=Scott R.|last11=Swanstrom|first11=Jesica|last12=Sheahan|first12=Timothy P.|last13=Pickles|first13=Raymond J.|last14=Corti|first14=Davide|last15=Randell|first15=Scott H.
|displayauthors=8|last16=Lanzavecchia|first16=Antonio|last17=Marasco|first17=Wayne A.|last18=Baric|first18=Ralph S.|title=SARS-like WIV1-CoV poised for human emergence|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences|volume=113|issue=11|year=2016|pages=3048–3053|issn=0027-8424|doi=10.1073/pnas.1517719113}}</ref><ref name="MenacheryYount2015">{{cite journal|last1=Menachery|first1=Vineet D|last2=Yount|first2=Boyd L|last3=Debbink|first3=Kari|last4=Agnihothram|first4=Sudhakar|last5=Gralinski|first5=Lisa E|last6=Plante|first6=Jessica A|last7=Graham|first7=Rachel L|last8=Scobey|first8=Trevor|last9=Ge|first9=Xing-Yi|last10=Donaldson|first10=Eric F|last11=Randell|first11=Scott H|last12=Lanzavecchia|first12=Antonio|last13=Marasco|first13=Wayne A|last14=Shi|first14=Zhengli-Li|last15=Baric|first15=Ralph S|title=A SARS-like cluster of circulating bat coronaviruses shows potential for human emergence|journal=Nature Medicine|volume=21|issue=12|year=2015|pages=1508–1513|issn=1078-8956|doi=10.1038/nm.3985}}</ref>；2016年發表了迄今發現與SARS-CoV全基因組相似度最高的蝙蝠病毒[[WIV16病毒|WIV16病毒]]，相似度達96%，為自雲南的中華菊頭蝠身上發現<ref name="pmid26719272"/>；2017年發表了自雲南一處洞窟中的菊頭蝠（中華菊頭蝠為主）發現的多個病毒株，包括與SARS-CoV分別在基因組各區域高度相似者，顯示SARS-CoV可能是由這些病毒株（或相關病毒株）經基因重組產生<ref name="pmid29190287">{{cite journal | author=Hu B, Zeng LP, Yang XL, Ge XY, Zhang W, Li B | display-authors=etal | title=Discovery of a rich gene pool of bat SARS-related coronaviruses provides new insights into the origin of SARS coronavirus. | journal=PLoS Pathog | year=2017 | volume=13 | issue=11 | pages=e1006698 | pmid=29190287 | doi=10.1371/journal.ppat.1006698 | pmc=5708621 | url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=29190287 | access-date=2021-07-09 | archive-date=2021-07-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709094546/https://journals.plos.org/plospathogens/article?id=10.1371%2Fjournal.ppat.1006698 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。以上蝙蝠病毒株的發現，皆支持中華菊頭蝠可能為感染人類的SARS-CoV之源頭，其病毒株經多次基因重組後[[病原溢出|溢出]]至市場中的[[果子貍|果子貍]]（[[果子狸SARS冠狀病毒|果子狸SARS冠狀病毒]]），再傳播給人類<ref name="Wang">{{cite journal |doi=10.3201/eid1212.060401 |pmid=17326933 |pmc=3291347 |title=Review of Bats and SARS |journal=Emerging Infectious Diseases |volume=12 |issue=12 |pages=1834–1840 |year=2006 |last1=Wang |first1=Lin-Fa |last2=Shi |first2=Zhengli |last3=Zhang|first3=Shuyi |last4=Field |first4=Hume |last5=Daszak |first5=Peter |last6=Eaton |first6=Bryan}}</ref><ref name="pmid20016037">{{cite journal | author=Yuan J, Hon CC, Li Y, Wang D, Xu G, Zhang H | display-authors=etal | title=Intraspecies diversity of SARS-like coronaviruses in Rhinolophus sinicus and its implications for the origin of SARS coronaviruses in humans. | journal=J Gen Virol | year=2010 | volume=91 | issue=Pt 4 | pages=1058-62 | pmid=20016037 | doi=10.1099/vir.0.016378-0 | pmc= | url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=20016037 | access-date=2021-07-09 | archive-date=2021-07-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709094531/https://www.microbiologyresearch.org/content/journal/jgv/10.1099/vir.0.016378-0 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

{{SARS-CoV-1 related coronavirus}}

[[File:SARS-CoV-2_without_background.png|thumb]]]]
2020年1月[[2019冠状病毒病疫情|2019冠状病毒病疫情]]甫爆發時，研究人員發現自浙江舟山菊頭蝠中發現的[[ZC45病毒與ZXC21病毒|ZC45病毒與ZXC21病毒]]是當時已知核酸序列與造成疫情之[[SARS-CoV-2|SARS-CoV-2]]最接近的病毒，相似度約為88%<ref name="JiangDu2020">{{cite journal|last1=Jiang|first1=Shibo|last2=Du|first2=Lanying|last3=Shi|first3=Zhengli|title=An emerging coronavirus causing pneumonia outbreak in Wuhan, China: calling for developing therapeutic and prophylactic strategies|journal=Emerging Microbes & Infections|volume=9|issue=1|year=2020|pages=275–277|issn=2222-1751|doi=10.1080/22221751.2020.1723441}}</ref>，但不久後即發現自[[雲南|雲南]][[中菊頭蝠|中菊頭蝠]]樣本中採集的[[RaTG13病毒|RaTG13病毒]]和SARS-CoV-2相似度更高，達96.2%，SARS-CoV-2很可能起源自菊頭蝠<ref name="ZhouYang2020">{{cite journal|last1=Zhou|first1=Peng|last2=Yang|first2=Xing-Lou|last3=Wang|first3=Xian-Guang|last4=Hu|first4=Ben|last5=Zhang|first5=Lei|last6=Zhang|first6=Wei|last7=Si|first7=Hao-Rui|last8=Zhu|first8=Yan|last9=Li|first9=Bei|last10=Huang|first10=Chao-Lin|last11=Chen|first11=Hui-Dong|last12=Chen|first12=Jing|last13=Luo|first13=Yun|last14=Guo|first14=Hua|last15=Jiang|first15=Ren-Di|last16=Liu|first16=Mei-Qin|last17=Chen|first17=Ying|last18=Shen|first18=Xu-Rui|last19=Wang|first19=Xi|last20=Zheng|first20=Xiao-Shuang|last21=Zhao|first21=Kai|last22=Chen|first22=Quan-Jiao|last23=Deng|first23=Fei|last24=Liu|first24=Lin-Lin|last25=Yan|first25=Bing|last26=Zhan|first26=Fa-Xian|last27=Wang|first27=Yan-Yi|last28=Xiao|first28=Geng-Fu|last29=Shi|first29=Zheng-Li|displayauthors=8|title=A pneumonia outbreak associated with a new coronavirus of probable bat origin|journal=Nature|volume=579|issue=7798|year=2020|pages=270–273|issn=0028-0836|doi=10.1038/s41586-020-2012-7}}</ref>，但傳播至人類的途徑仍不明朗，隨後又有另一種自雲南[[馬來亞菊頭蝠|馬來亞菊頭蝠]]身上採得的冠狀病毒（[[RmYN02病毒|RmYN02病毒]]）發表<ref name="ZhouChen2020"/>。[[中國海關|中國海關]]截獲自東南亞走私的[[馬來穿山甲|馬來穿山甲]]因也帶有和SARS-CoV-2相似的病毒（[[穿山甲冠狀病毒|穿山甲冠狀病毒]]），被懷疑為其[[中間宿主|中間宿主]]<ref name="MacKenzie">{{cite journal|doi=10.1071/MA20013|title=COVID-19: A novel zoonotic disease caused by a coronavirus from China: What we know and what we don't|year=2020|last1=MacKenzie|first1=John S.|last2=Smith|first2=David W.|journal=Microbiology Australia|volume=41|pages=45|pmid=32226946|pmc=7086482|quote=Evidence from the sequence analyses clearly indicates that the reservoir host of the virus was a bat, probably a Chinese or Intermediate horseshoe bat, and it is probable that, like SARS-CoV, an intermediate host was the source of the outbreak.}}</ref>，但仍未被證實<ref name="Boni">{{cite journal|doi=10.1038/s41564-020-0771-4|title=Evolutionary origins of the SARS-CoV-2 sarbecovirus lineage responsible for the COVID-19 pandemic|year=2020|last1=Boni|first1=Maciej F.|last2=Lemey|first2=Philippe|last3=Jiang|first3=Xiaowei|last4=Lam|first4=Tommy Tsan-Yuk|last5=Perry|first5=Blair W.|last6=Castoe|first6=Todd A.|last7=Rambaut|first7=Andrew|last8=Robertson|first8=David L.|s2cid=220809302|journal=Nature Microbiology|volume=5|issue=11|pages=1408–1417|pmid=32724171|doi-access=free}}</ref>。後來日本、柬埔寨與泰國的菊頭蝠中也發現了和SARS-CoV-2相似的冠狀病毒<ref name="MurakamiKitamura2020"/<ref name=RshSTT/<ref name=RacCS203/>。

{{SARS-CoV-2 related coronavirus}}

====其他病毒====
[[File:Rhinolophus_rouxii.jpg|thumb]]
除冠狀病毒外，菊頭蝠身上還可能帶有[[正呼腸孤病毒屬|正呼腸孤病毒]]、{{tsl|en|Flavivirus|黃熱病毒屬|黃熱病毒}}或[[漢他病毒|漢他病毒]]等其他病毒。小菊頭蝠與小蹄鼻蝠身上曾發現帶有不同類型的{{le|哺乳动物正呼肠孤病毒|Mammalian orthoreovirus}}（MRV），但尚無證據顯示其可感染人類<ref>{{cite book |title=Bats and Human Health: Ebola, SARS, Rabies and Beyond |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OK45DwAAQBAJ&pg=PA155 |page=155 |first=Lisa A. |last=Beltz |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |year=2017 |isbn=9781119150046 |access-date=2021-06-11 |archive-date=2021-06-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210616155337/https://books.google.com/books?id=OK45DwAAQBAJ&pg=PA155 |dead-url=no }}</ref>；印度南部的[[魯氏菊頭蝠|魯氏菊頭蝠]]身上曾被發現帶有可造成一種[[蜱|蜱]]傳[[病毒性出血熱|病毒性出血熱]]的{{tsl|en|Kyasanur Forest disease|凯萨努森林病|凯萨努森林病毒}}（屬黃熱病毒）<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1002/rmv.495 |pmid=16710839 |title=Kyasanur forest disease: An epidemiological view in India |journal=Reviews in Medical Virology |volume=16 |issue=3 |pages=151–165 |year=2006 |last=Pattnaik |first=Priyabrata|s2cid=32814428 }}</ref>；中國的中菊頭蝠、中華菊頭蝠與[[角菊頭蝠|角菊頭蝠]]身上曾發現有[[龍泉病毒|龍泉病毒]]（屬漢他病毒）<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1371/journal.ppat.1003159 |pmid=23408889 |pmc=3567184 |title=Phylogeny and Origins of Hantaviruses Harbored by Bats, Insectivores, and Rodents |year=2013 |last1=Guo |first1=Wen-Ping |last2=Lin |first2=Xian-Dan |last3=Wang |first3=Wen |last4=Tian |first4=Jun-Hua |last5=Cong |first5=Mei-Li |last6=Zhang |first6=Hai-Lin |last7=Wang |first7=Miao-Ruo |last8=Zhou |first8=Run-Hong |last9=Wang |first9=Jian-Bo |last10=Li |first10=Ming-Hui |last11=Xu |first11=Jianguo |last12=Holmes |first12=Edward C. |author-link12=Edward C. Holmes |last13=Zhang |first13=Yong-Zhen |author-link13=张永振|journal=PLOS Pathogens |volume=9 |issue=2 |pages=e1003159}}</ref>。

===藥用與食用===
{{main|食用蝙蝠}}
相較於大型蝙蝠，菊頭蝠等小型蝙蝠較少被人類作為食物來源，但仍有許多物種在[[漠南非洲|漠南非洲]]與東南亞被人類獵食，在非洲被食用的物種包括{{le|魚狗菊頭蝠|Halcyon horseshoe bat}}、{{le|幾內亞菊頭蝠|Guinean horseshoe bat}}、{{le|林菊头蝠|Rhinolophus silvestris}}、''{{le|Rhinolophus hilli}}''、''{{le|Rhinolophus maclaudi}}''與''{{le|Rhinolophus ziama}}''，{{le|馬氏菊頭蝠|Rhinolophus marshalli}}與{{le|广鞍菊头蝠|Rhinolophus rufus}}則分別在[[緬甸|緬甸]]和[[菲律賓|菲律賓]]被食用<ref name="Mildenstein">{{cite book |doi=10.1007/978-3-319-25220-9_12 |chapter=Exploitation of bats for bushmeat and medicine |title=Bats in the Anthropocene: Conservation of Bats in a Changing World |pages=327 |year=2016 |last1=Mildenstein |first1=T. |last2=Tanshi |first2=I. |last3=Racey |first3=P. A. |publisher=Springer |isbn=978-3-319-25218-6|s2cid=130038936 }}</ref>。

除食用外，菊頭蝠還在亞洲與非洲被用來入藥，印度東北部的{{le|阿沃-那加人|Ao Naga}}有用菊頭蝠的肉來治療[[哮喘|哮喘]]的紀錄；[[尼泊爾|尼泊爾]]的[[內瓦爾人|內瓦爾人]]用菊頭蝠與蹄蝠來製作「蝙蝠油」（Cikā Lāpa Wasa），將蝙蝠的屍體浸泡在密封的[[芥子油|芥子油]]中製成，蝙蝠油被當地人用來治療「耳蟲」（可能為傳統文化中對[[偏頭痛|偏頭痛]]的解釋）、禿頭和麻痺等疾患<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.2993/0278-0771(2008)28[69:TUOBAM]2.0.CO;2 |issn=0278-0771 |year=2008 |volume=28 |pages=69–91 |title=The Use of Bats as Medicine Among the Newars |journal=Journal of Ethnobiology |last1=Tuladhar-Douglas |first1=Will}}</ref>。[[塞內加爾|塞內加爾]]據傳有{{le|馬拉博特|marabout}}（伊斯蘭修士）用{{le|煙熏菊頭蝠|Rhinolophus fumigatus}}製作藥水來治療精神疾病者；[[越南|越南]]則有一生技公司每年使用多達50公噸菊頭蝠的糞便製藥<ref>{{cite journal | last1= Riccucci | first1= M. | year= 2012 | title= Bats as materia medica: An ethnomedical review and implications for conservation | journal= Vespertillio | volume= 16 | issue= 16 | pages= 249–270 | url= https://www.researchgate.net/publication/235990579 | access-date= 2021-06-11 | archive-date= 2021-07-09 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210709094604/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/235990579_Bats_as_materia_medica_an_ethnomedical_review_and_implications_for_conservation | dead-url= no }}</ref>。

==保育==
截至2020年，[[國際自然保護聯盟|國際自然保護聯盟]]（IUCN）已評估了92種菊頭蝠的保育狀況，結果如下<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iucnredlist.org/search|website=IUCN|access-date=2020-12-14|title=<nowiki>Taxonomy=Rhinolophidae</nowiki>|archive-date=2019-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915111441/https://www.iucnredlist.org/search|dead-url=no}}</ref>：
*[[極危物種|極危物種]]：1種（''Rhinolophus hilli''）
*[[瀕危物種|瀕危物種]]：13種
*[[易危物種|易危物種]]：9種
*[[近危物種|近危物種]]：4種
*[[無危物種|無危物種]]：51種
*[[數據缺乏|數據缺乏]]：14種

菊頭蝠與其他棲息於洞窟中的蝙蝠一樣受到蝙蝠糞開採、[[石灰岩|石灰岩]]開採與洞窟旅遊等人類活動造成的[[棲地破壞|棲地干擾]]<ref name="Furey"/>。

